class_name WorldLoreExtended
# Extended lore entries — district histories, faction origins, companion lore

const DISTRICT_HISTORIES: Dictionary = {
	"paw_vegas": """Paws Vegas began as a single card table operated by a cat named Dealer Dev in year one.
By year three, it had expanded to occupy an entire district. The SovereignCrown saw opportunity
and quietly purchased controlling interest in seven establishments. Today, the neon lights never
dim and the dice never stop rolling. The mysterious cat in the corner has been there since the beginning.
No one knows who they are. Dev has stopped asking.""",

	"cat_coliseum": """The Coliseum predates the factions. Ancient records describe frame-based combat
as a sacred ritual — Light against Heavy against Tech — before it became spectacle.
Coach Mira claims to have fought in the original matches. Champion Vex has never commented.
The grand prize, the Sovereign Frame, appears in the records once. It disappeared the same day.""",

	"neon_alley": """The canals of Neon Alley were built by the VeiledCurrent before they became a faction.
They claim the water carries information — trading routes, movement patterns, secrets.
Whether this is metaphor or fact is unclear. Race Starter Nara runs the circuit with mechanical precision.
The entry fees never change. The canal never floods. The Current controls both.""",

	"cat_forest": """The forest is older than the city. Forest Elder Moss has lived here since
before Paws Vegas was built. The WildlandsAscendant grew from a small tribe of cats
who refused to leave when construction began. They stayed. The forest stayed.
The 500 companions recorded in ancient texts are still out there. Companion Keeper Zara
has documented 432 of them personally. She will not discuss the other 68.""",

	"arcade_galaxy": """No one built the Arcade Galaxy. It appeared. That's the official record.
Arcade Host Pixel claims to have been there when it materialized — a Tuesday, they say,
just after midnight. The games inside follow rules that exist nowhere else.
Puzzle Master Gridlock arrived three days after it appeared and has not left since.
Scientists have declined to investigate. The games are too good.""",
}

const FACTION_ORIGINS: Dictionary = {
	"SovereignCrown": """Founded by a gambler known only as 'the Sovereign' who won controlling
interest in Paws Vegas in a single hand of poker. The Crown's philosophy is simple:
control the table and you control the game. Their combat advantage reflects this —
they train harder, equip better, and never leave anything to chance. Their companions
tend toward heavy frames and raw power. The SovereignCrown does not believe in luck.
They manufacture it.""",

	"WildlandsAscendant": """Born from the Forest cats who watched Paws Vegas consume the land
around them. Their leader, Forest Elder Moss, chose a third path: not conquest, not submission,
but cultivation. The WildlandsAscendant train with the forest's rhythms — speed over strength,
adaptability over brute force. Their race speed bonus is no accident; they've been running
these paths since before the first road was paved. Their companions are fast, wild, and deeply loyal.""",

	"VeiledCurrent": """The Current predates the other factions by decades. They built the canals.
They established the trade routes. When the other factions rose to power, the Current simply
smiled and continued their work. Their luck bonus is real — they've spent generations studying
probability, patterns, and the mathematics of chance. A VeiledCurrent companion by your side
doesn't just bring luck. It brings the Current's accumulated knowledge of when to act
and when to wait.""",

	"Factionless": """Not everyone chose a side. The Factionless are the ones who looked at all
three factions and said 'no.' Some are philosophers. Some are survivors. Some are simply
cats who value freedom above alliance. Their companions are diverse — drawn from every
background, every type, every rarity. There are legendary Factionless companions that
no faction has been able to recruit. The Unchained. The Last Freecat. They answer to no one.
Their stat spread is balanced, their loyalty unconditional, their price... negotiable.""",
}

